<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-06T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-06T16:00:00-05:00" n="454" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/7581</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SFJ1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-06T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 6, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your November 5, 11 a.m. Department considers it inadvisable for you to
                            attend conference to which you refer. You are directed to make no
                            expressions of opinion either personally or officially in connection
                            with this matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>